The paper discusses the current state and problems of artificial intelligence, specifically in the domain of language processing. This suggests that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of AI (cs.AI), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes an alternative approach that involves philosophy, which could potentially fall under the sub-categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
